'Nipper' (1884–1895) was a dog who served as the model for a painting titled His
Master's Voice. This image was the basis for the dog and gramophone logo used by
several audio recording and associated brands: His Master's Voice, HMV, EMI,
RCA, Victor Talking Machine Company, RCA Victor, JVC and Deutsche Grammophon.
